<P>
   BKN-PACERS (Indianapolis) _ The game was in the vault an hour
before. Reggie Miller had pulled the pin on his last 3-pointer, and
Jalen Rose had peeled and sliced a defense purported to be the
league's most stingy. So all the two emotional scorers had left to
do was not anger the gods any further, be happy with their 33-point
knockout over Shaquille O'Neal, Kobe Bryant and the Los Angeles
Lakers in Game 5 of the National Basketball Association finals.
Catch a flight to Los Angeles for Game 6. Maybe a humble statement
or two, and that's it. Move on. But they could not help themselves.
By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-LAKERS (Indianapolis) _ So much for the Los Angeles Lakers'
new-found ability to close out a series. With an opportunity to
close out the Indiana Pacers at Conseco Fieldhouse in Game 5 Friday
night and garner their first NBA title since 1988, the Lakers
stumbled horribly. It wasn't the first time. By Chris Broussard.
</P>
