   BBO-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Lead item: In the words of an executive
with a competing club, ``They changed everything from top to bottom
and they wind up with the same animal.'' The animal that is the
Colorado Rockies, though, is a more attractive species this season.
Many of the Rockies' ingredients look similar to last year, but the
team has made impressive improvements in some key areas, and the
difference is in the standings. By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ NASCAR officials this week had to
review videotape of yet another horrific accident. The latest
involved Elliott Sadler, a 25-year-old in just his second full
season in the Winston Cup Series. As the NASCAR world knows all too
acutely, Adam Petty was not as fortunate as Sadler, who walked away
with a few bruises. Petty, the 19-year-old, fourth generation
driver was killed during practice at New Hampshire International
Speedway last month, after hitting a wall. By Charlie Nobles.
</P>
