<HEADLINE>
WE'VE GOT AN IPO YOU CAN'T REFUSE 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For use by special arrangement
only. Asian and European points: Call Karl Horwitz in Paris for
details and prices, phone: 47 42 17 11; fax: 47-42-80-44). Latin
American points: Call Olivia Vasquez in Los Angeles, phone:
310-996-0075; fax: 310-996-0089). 
(Eds: Text in boldface should be set in italics.) 
 By JOE SHARKEY    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   TO: Members of the Commission &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FROM: Vinnie ``Sausage Lips'' Dellicatessio, chairman, La Cosa
Nostra 2000 committee
</P>
<P>
   RE: Update on New Lines of Business
</P>
<P>
   As you would of heard by now, the recent LCN 2000 initiative to
increase annual revenue by hustling stocks to greedy investors met
with a setback last week due to unforeseen federal indictments. We
see this as another misguided attempt by headline-hunting
prosecutors to discourage innovation and limit competition in the
growing global organized-crime business. Be that as it may, I am
pleased to give you this update on various other LCN 2000 strategic
business initiatives, all firmly anchored to our well-established
brand names:
</P>
<P>
   HELLO? OMERTA CALLING! _ Keyed off our trademarked Code of
Silence, we offer a service to clients who are irritated by those
rude people using their cell phones at theaters, in restaurants and
elsewhere. Just dial 1-800-SILENCE, provide a (legit only!)
credit-card number, and presto: An Omerta agent, like our New York
rapid-response rep Santore ``Crunchie'' Multimalo, arrives on the
scene, forcibly removes the cell phone from the offending party and
_ here's the beautiful part _ eats it.
</P>
<P>
   MAFIONYMS _ Ever since Joe Valachi started squealing in the
1960s, Americans have been fascinated by mob nicknames. Until now,
these monikers have been strictly reserved for our own associates.
But now, with Mafionyms, anyone can join the fun! Just stop by for
a personal consultation at a convenient Mafionym(R) kiosk at your
local shopping mall. Badda-bing, badda-bang, badda-boom, you walk
away with your very own mob nickname _ just like the real ones.
Testimonials from happy customers are pouring in:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``I adore the feeling of being so, like, connected!!!''  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Sue-Emily ``Really White Sneakers'' Reynolds, Santa Barbara,
CA.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The guy in the next cubicle? Green with envy.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Brad ``Flamer'' Tinkley Harris, Worcester, MA.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``My new Mafionym(R) drives my mother crazy!'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Lonnie ``Always With the Decaf'' Latoosh, Philadelphia, PA.
</P>
<P>
   AQUA PERSUASION _ You might of read in the paper last week that
some fancy restaurants are pressuring customers to order expensive
bottled water to pad those dinner and lunch checks. Overworked
small-restaurant owners without pushy staff can now hustle the H20
just like the big joints. Simply call in our Aqua Persuasion(R)
sales team! Our surly bruisers will arrive tableside wearing
T-shirts that say, ``Excuse me, you  &UR; are &LR;  having the bottled
water.'' Watch those bottles of Evian and Pellegrino move!
</P>
<P>
   (Also on the food-service front, LCN 2000 will soon announce
details of our latest strategic restaurant initiative, in
partnership with one of our Brooklyn dessert-foods subsidiaries: I
SCREAM, YOU SCREAM, YOU BETTER STOCK THIS ICE CREAM(R).)
</P>
<P>
   COVER ME, OR TALK TO THEM _ Tired of pleading with those
passive-aggressives at your HMO who refuse to approve treatment for
that pesky heart attack or broken leg? Just call Cover Me or Talk
to Them(R) and our specially trained HMO negotiators will get right
on the case! Within hours, those HMO chumps will display a new
understanding of terms like necessary procedure and
hospitalization. Know what I mean? No paperwork!
</P>
<P>
   As you can see, we here at LCN 2000 are neither resting on our
laurels nor going to the mattresses as we look at the exciting
challenges facing the commission in this high-tech, entrepreneurial
world. Look for lots of exciting news in coming months, including
our long-planned entry in the Internet security field with our
initial public offering, I-GOT-YOUR-VIRUS-RIGHT-HERE.COM. And
development is well underway for two new network game shows, ``Who
Wants to Rob a Millionaire?'' and ``Survive This!''
</P>
<P>
   Also in the works is ``Knock Knock, This Is Your Life,'' a
reality-based show in which some of the boys make a surprise visit
each week to various old friends currently in the federal witness
protection program.
</P>
<P>
   So what if we took a hit in the stock market! Our future is
bright, gentlemen, because we're organized, we're flexible, we're
LCN 2000, the family brand.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
