   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   SYRIA-BASHAR _ QARDAHA, Syria _ The mindset in this remote
mountain village _ birthplace of late Syrian President Hafez Assad
_ is indicative of why it will be difficult for heir-apparent Bahar
Assad to compromise in the Middle East peace process. At the mosque
where the elder Assad's funeral was held last week, the imam _ or
priest _ has a short answer for what people here would think of any
leader who settles for anything less than the entire Golan Heights:
``He would be a traitor.'' Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
</P>
