<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   LOS-ALAMOS-SCENE _ SANTA FE, N.M. _ First came the spy scandal.
Then the wildfire that almost swallowed them whole. Now, secret
nuclear files from Division ``X'' are missing. Over the past year,
event after event has dropped like bombs over America's Atomic
City, shaking up the isolated, orderly existence this northern New
Mexico town and its nuclear weapons laboratory have enjoyed for
more than half a century. Once the very center of the world's
scientific research, Los Alamos has become an embarrassment - and
once-proud town residents are taking it on the chin. (Guthrie,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 70.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This story can be found on the WAN in the Atlanta Location
with a category of Lifestyle.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-VEEP _ Behind the scenes, as quietly and deliberately as
possible, Gov. George W. Bush is exercising the most power power
granted to any one person in a democracy. In picking a running
mate, Bush will have the one-man authority to grant near-world
leader status to the person of his choice. It's a delicate exercise
devoid of checks and
</P>
<P>
   balances other than the electorate that involves considerable
political risk. A look at how Bush is doing it. (Herman, Austin
American-Statesman). 35. MOVED Friday in (p) Politics and (a)
General News categories.
</P>
<P>
   DAVIDIAN-STAKES _ WACO, Texas _ A look at the issues _ legal,
financial, symbolic, philosophical _ at stake in the Branch
Davidian civil trial. (England, Waco Tribune-Herald).
