<P>
   SEMINARY-PRESIDENT _ Decatur, Ga. _ Laura S. Mendenhall is
expected to be elected the eighth president of Columbia Theological
Seminary in Decatur, Ga., by the seminary's Board of Trustees on
Saturday. Dr. Mendenhall is pastor of Westminster Presbyterian
Church, Austin, Texas. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   LABOR-SWEENEY _ The American labor movement, once drifting
toward irrelevancy, is surging with new energy under the leadership
of AFL-CIO President John Sweeney. No where is labor's new potency
and political clout more on display than in Los Angeles, where
union membership swelled by 91,000 people last year, the most of
anywhere in the country. New immigrants account for much of labor's
increase and their numbers have helped the Democrats reclaim all
three branches of California's government. This year, the AFL-CIO
is poised to reverse a long-standing policy opposing amnesty for
immigrants in a move that reflects how important immigrant workers
have become to labor's economic and political future. (Foskett,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 60.
</P>
<P>
   CHRISTOPHER_ WASHINGTON _ Vice President Al Gore is turning to a
man whose judgment he trusts to help him choose a running mate _
Warren Christopher, who ran the selection process that put Gore on
the ticket with Bill Clinton. (Shepard, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location Atlanta, category National, subcategory Politics.
</P>
<P>
   Moving on NYT wire in (w) Washington and (p) politics
categories.
</P>
<P>
   FATHERS-VIETNAM _ WASHINGTON _ More than 1,000 sons and
daughters of soldiers whose names are inscribed on the Vietnam
Memorial are attending a reunion that will culminate in a Father's
Day ceremony at the memorial. (Dart, Cox News Service). Photos
MOVED Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   MOVED on NYT wire in (w) Washington and (l) lifestyle
categories.
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location Atlanta, category National, subcategory Other.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-CHENEY _ George W. Bush's one-man vice presidential search
committee comes battle-tested and with mom's seal of approval.
Former Defense Secretary Dick Cheney is ``as competent as they
come,'' Barbara Bush wrote in her diary on March 2, 1991 as the
success of Operation Desert Storm had become apparent. (Austin
American-Statesman). MOVED Friday in (p) Politics and (a) General
News categories.
</P>
<P>
   JAZZ-CAMP _ BIRMINGHAM - The neck of his Fender Jazz Bass seems
almost too long for Jason Turner. He squeezes down the note for a
blues arrangement, looking as if he were holding a dance partner
too tall for him. Turner has played bass for just a year. But the
13-year-old has rhythm. During an improve class at the 11th-annual
City Stages summer jazz camp, he is rhythm. With nearly 100 other
summer campers, Turner is learning how to swing. Professional
musicians are training aspiring jazz artists who will perform today
(Saturday) at a downtown music festival. You see, this is your
grandmother's jazz. Dixieland. Blues. It's the smoking riffs built
in the Deep South in the early 1900s. This is the stuff of Louis
Armstrong, John Coltrane, Miles Davis, Ella Fitzgerald. This is not
the commercial fluff from, say, Kenny G. (Manuel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15. MOVED Friday in (a) General News and (l)
Lifestyles categories.
</P>
