<P>
   JAZZLAND _ NEW ORLEANS _ Checking out Jazzland theme park, with
six themed sections containing 30 rides, shows, food and music _
all with a Louisiana flavor.
</P>
<P>
   Teases inside to tour story. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) MOVED Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, June 18.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   JAZZTOUR _ NEW ORLEANS _ A long day at Jazzland theme park in
New Orleans: We arrived when the park opened at 10 a.m. and
stumbled out when it closed at 10 p.m. During those 12 hours, we
were drenched on the Spillway Splashdown, scared senseless on the
MegaZeph rollercoaster, tapped our toes to Zydeco music at the
Cajun Dance Hall, chowed down on Creole cuisine, saw the revue
``Jazz, Jazz, Jazz'' twice and tossed beads from the lead float in
the Mardi Gras parade. (Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
MOVED Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, June 18.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY _ Dozens of shops and galleries line the red-bricked
streets of Waynesville, N.C., where the annual summer Art Studios &AMP;
Gallery Tour will be June 17. Also, coming up in July, is the
annual Folkmoot International Festival which features 10 or 12
troupes from around the world. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
