Trail, stretching from Independence, Mo., to Oregon's Willamette
River Valley. For those who go for history, particularly Western
history, the Oregon Trail remains a fascinating trip. The route
crosses enough diverse landscapes _ many of them dizzyingly sublime
_ to make the journey across this pioneering American route, even
now, worth taking. (Chaffin, Atlanta Journal-Constitution
freelancer; not for use by NYTNS clients.)
