<P>
   BOOKS-WALKER _ LUFKIN, Texas _ Singer/Songwriter Jerry Jeff
Walker was born and spent his early years in a small upstate New
York town. While still in his teens, he traveled across country
many items, stopping along the way in such diverse places as Key
West, Florida, New Orleans and Greenwich Village, Manhattan. At
each stopover, he learned new songs, new ways to sing them and new
guitar licks to stir into his developing style as a ``songman.''
The songs he wrote as he traveled tell the story of his life and
way of living and making music. Now, he's written this book that
fills in the details. It's a fascinating tale, whether or not you
are a Jerry Jeff fan. (Milner, Lufkin Daily News). MOVED.
