<P>
   WEB-MOVIES _ The Internet's embrace of movies isn't in the
future. It's right now. At least a dozen Web sites (like
cinemanow.com, mediatrip.com and thenewvenue.com) feature movie
shorts and/or full-length flicks that film fans can watch for free.
For Hollywood studios, ``there's an element of panic,'' says
director Mike Figgis, whose recent ``Time Code'' illustrates
another aspect of filmmaking challenging conventional Hollywood _
digital technology. ``There's a real nervousness because they
regard the technology and the people who come with it like the
rabble at the door of the castle.'' Many see a mad scramble for
``web site territory'' (cinemanow.com, for example, is an arm of
Trimark). (BLonginio, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16. MOVED.
</P>
